<span style="font-weight: 400;">Emphysema is a condition in which the breathing tubes in the lungs are narrowed and the air sacs are stretched and damaged due to excessive smoking or passive smoking.Â </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Emphysema is a form of COPD. Chronic Bronchitis, which is another form of COPD, differs from Emphysema in that a lot of mucus is formed in Chronic Bronchitis while Emphysema is mainly characterised by shortness of breath even while doing the simplest of works.</span>

