<b>Symptoms</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">It usually starts with shortness of breath which can lead to bigger problems. You might just ignore it considering it to be your age or health status but it affects your oxygen intake levels and hence your bloodstream. Emphysema makes it hard to catch your breath even after doing the easiest of jobs. Most people with emphysema also suffer from chronic bronchitis. (Search Bronchitis and COPD)</span>

<b>Â A few preventive measures one can take are:</b>
<ul>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â  Â  Avoid passive smoking</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â  Â  Wear a mask to eliminate dust and air pollution</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Â  Â  Exercise and try Yoga therapies to improve breathing</span></li>
</ul>
<b>Treatment</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Damaged lungs cannot be repaired (in some cases surgery or even lung transplant could be needed). Inhalers could be prescribed or even direct oxygen depending on the severity of the condition.</span>

<b>Lifestyle changes that can give some relief from Emphysema:</b>
<ol>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Quit smoking</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Follow a healthy diet</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Get some exercise everyday</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Keep fully hydrated - have warm water throughout the day - this will keep the airway free by loosening the mucus.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">When going out into the cold air, cover your nose and mouth with a scarf.</span></li>
</ol>
